Researchers in England and Wales found a strong link between schizophrenia and the age of fathers, with mutations in sperm contributing to the risk.
France, Britain, and the Czech Republic have high cannabis consumption rates, prompting a 10-million euro campaign in France to highlight its harmful effects.
Genetic research has identified a region on the 17th chromosome linked to schizophrenia, with implications for understanding brain deterioration in sufferers.
In Uganda, poverty, war, and lifestyle changes are cited as factors contributing to mental disorders.
IBM and EPFL scientists are collaborating to create a detailed model of the neocortex to simulate brain functions at a molecular level.
